HEADWORD: Giaour
<hw>Giaour</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Turk.
<ets>giaur</ets> an infidel, Per. <ets>gawr</ets>, another form of
<ets>ghebr</ets> fire worshiper. Cf. <er>Kaffir</er>, <er>Gheber</er>
.]</ety> <def>An infidel; -- a term applied by Turks to disbelievers in
the Muslim religion, especially Christians.</def>
<rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

